</section><section id="fs-idm180006288" class="section-summary">
<title>Summary of Learning Outcomes</title>
<list id="fs-idm173781552" list-type="enumerated" start-value="6">
<item>What are the types of compensation and methods for paying workers?</item>
</list>
<para id="fs-idm193879152">Direct pay is the hourly wage or monthly salary paid to an employee. In addition to the base wage or salary, direct pay may include bonuses and profit shares. Indirect pay consists of various benefits and services. Some benefits are required by law and include unemployment compensation, worker’s compensation, and Social Security. Many employers also offer benefits not required by law. These include paid vacations and holidays, pensions, health and other insurance, employee wellness programs, and college tuition reimbursement.</para>
</section>
